                <note rend="inline" type="source">791.003/79: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-10T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1928—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 10—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Department’s 20, March 3, 5 p.m. This matter has been informally discussed at
                    the German Foreign Office, and as a result the German Minister in Persia has
                    been telegraphically instructed to cooperate fully with his American
                    colleague.</p>
                <p>Although the German Government is in accord fundamentally with the British
                    memorandum and is convinced that harmonious action is needed among the western
                    powers, this Embassy today is informed that there exist some difficulties which
                    the German Foreign Office wishes next week informally to discuss with the
                    Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
